# Statements & history

## Statement ingestion (no browser)
- CSV/TSV: use `npm run ingest -- --bank <id> --file statements/<file>.csv`. It auto-detects
  common English/Spanish column names (date/fecha, description/concepto, debit/debito,
  credit/credito, amount/monto, currency/moneda). Override with `--date-col`, `--desc-col`,
  `--amount-col`, `--debit-col`, `--credit-col`, `--currency-col`. Duplicates (same
  date+amount+description+direction) are skipped automatically.
- PDF/images: read the file and write structured JSON into `input/banks/<id>.json` directly —
  there is no binary parser. Mask identifiers, use ISO dates, set currency + confidence.
- Never copy full account numbers from a statement; mask to `****1234`. After ingesting,
  run `npm run build && npm run validate && npm run audit`.

## History & trends (SQLite)
- `npm run db` writes the current `output/financial-snapshot.json` into `output/finance.db`
  (built on Node's `node:sqlite`; idempotent per `snapshot_date`).
- `npm run trends` prints cash / card-debt / loan-debt by currency across all snapshots.
- `output/finance.db` is git-ignored (real financial data). Snapshot history is also
  duplicated as timestamped files under `output/history/`.
